8";s:4:"item";s:7:"Get Out";s:12:"item_creator";s:1:"0";s:11:"description";s:852:"Get Out is a 2017 American horror film written and directed by Jordan Peele. It stars Daniel Kaluuya as Chris, a black man who notices unusual behavior from the black housekeeper and groundskeeper at the family home of his white girlfriend (Allison Williams). Bradley Whitford, Caleb Landry Jones, Stephen Root, and Catherine Keener co-star.

Get Out premiered at the Sundance Film Festival on January 24, 2017, and was theatrically released in the United States on February 24, 2017, by Universal Pictures. The film was praised by critics, particularly for Peele\'s screenplay and direction, and Kaluuya\'s performance. It was chosen by the National Board of Review, the American Film Institute, and Time magazine as one of the top 10 films of the year. The film was also a box office success, grossing $255 million worldwide on a $4.5 million budget.";s:10:"date_added";s:1:"0";s:8:"modified";N;s:11:"modified_by";N;s:5:"image";s:130:"a:2:{s:5:"image";s:34:"directcron/Horror_DVDs/get_out.png";s:9:"thumbnail";s:46:"directcron/Horror_DVDs//thumbnails/get_out.png";}";s:5:"video";N;s:8:"item_url";N;s:12:"templatefile";s:7:"oneitem";s:8:"metadesc";s:0:"";s:8:"meta_key";s:0:"";s:10:"searchkeys";N;s:6:"visits";s:1:"0";s:9:"published";s:1:"1";s:8:"ordering";s:1:"0";s:8:"featured";s:1:"0";s:14:"featured_order";s:1:"0";s:6:"access";s:6:"public";s:12:"published_up";s:19:"2018-02-13 02:03:58";s:14:"published_down";N;}}');

